<p>The life cycle of a directly transmited pathogen is governed by its birth and death rates (λ and 
 <italic>μ</italic>, respectively). In the absence of seasonality these birth and death rates are constant (λ &gt; 0, 
 <italic>μ</italic> &gt; 0), the basic reproduction number is 
 <inline-formula id="pcbi.1007954.e016">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1007954.e016.jpg" id="pcbi.1007954.e016g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M16">
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>R</mi>
      <mn>0</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mo>λ</mo>
      <mi>μ</mi>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> and the probability of extinction, starting initially with one individual, is 
 <inline-formula id="pcbi.1007954.e017">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1007954.e017.jpg" id="pcbi.1007954.e017g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M17">
    <mrow>
     <mi>q</mi>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mo form="prefix" movablelimits="true">inf</mo>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <msub>
       <mi>R</mi>
       <mn>0</mn>
      </msub>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> (
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="pcbi.1007954.g001">Fig 1</xref>). This result was first derived by [
 <xref rid="pcbi.1007954.ref040" ref-type="bibr">40</xref>].
</p>
